# Digital Certificates

## Overview

A digital certificate is an electronic document that verifies the identity of a person, device, or organization by binding its identity to a public key. Digital certificates are issued and digitally signed by a trusted Certificate Authority (CA).

Digital certificates are a fundamental part of Public Key Infrastructure (PKI).

## Key Concepts

- Public Key
- Certificate Authority (CA)
- Digital Signature
- Subject
- Expiration Date

## Why It Matters

Digital certificates allow users and systems to verify that they are communicating with the intended party rather than an impersonator. They establish trust for secure communication over untrusted networks.

## Common Uses

- HTTPS Websites
- TLS
- VPNs
- Secure Email
- Code Signing
- Device Authentication

## Best Practices

- Obtain certificates from trusted Certificate Authorities.
- Protect the associated private key.
- Renew certificates before they expire.
- Revoke compromised certificates immediately.
- Validate certificates before trusting them.

